Our server Jordan was a delight. He gave a great description of the specials off the top of his head with his own personal touches. I was being finicky (I know, not a good look) and requested a taste of one of the wines they had on special, which he happily provided. We both got the featured red wine and received a generous “small” pour.  The table bread and olive oil is too good as it’s easy to eat the whole loaf! We started with the Insalata della Casa appetizer and it was sooooo good. My friend and I kept saying after every bite how delicious it was. Move over Brussels sprouts, this artichoke app is the new game in town! Entrees were awesome. I loved my pasta with sausage and veggies. I’ve had it the past three times I’ve been there and I can never remember the name of the dish but it’s excellent. Pasta is cooked perfectly al dente.  For dessert we split the flourless chocolate lava cake and added an extra scoop of vanilla ice cream. It hit the spot along with my espresso martini.  Meal was plenty filling and we both took leftovers home and it didn’t break the bank. Will be back again!

The atmosphere, the service, the food, all three are just wonderful. When you walk in, you just know you’re going to be treated right. I had been to Francesca’s North growing up in Northbrook, and I didn’t realize they were the same company. It totally makes sense though, Mia’s is everything that North is, but better. The location is perfect, it’s exactly where it needs to be while also being almost a hidden a gem. But there’s nothing hidden about it when you walk inside, this is Italy. You know as soon as you walk in, what to expect. When I’m there it’s like I’m family, from my very first visit. It doesn’t matter which server I get, they all are on top of it every time. Never hovering but always there when needed. The management does a great training their staff. The general manager, I believe his name is Peter, always makes sure to stop by the table and check in on us. All I can ever tell him is how good everything is. And that brings me to the food, Chicago is an Italian city among other things, and you can taste the roots when you come here. My scale doesn’t like it when I come here, but that’s because I need to have every course. My favorites are calamari to share, followed by the Caesar Salad, with the Ravioli All’emiliana as my entree. I’m just stuffed after this, but how can I not get dessert when it’s the perfect tiramisu? The trick is to take a little but home of every course so you can make it through, and then it’s like a sampling the next day when you get to relive your dining experience with your leftovers. 5 out of 5, see you again soon!

Very good place but with a small caveat.   I got the flat iron steak with mushrooms and truffle fries.   My wife got a cannelloni dish and we split a side of sauteed shrimp.  The flat iron steak was cooked correctly and had great flavor.   The mushrooms were outstanding. The truffle fries were great...till I got to the ones at the bottom of the fry pile soaked in juices and oil.  Soggy but good flavor.  The shrimp were some of the better shrimp my wife and I have ever had, being perfectly cooked.... but there were only three.  They should have a shrimp only dish with angel hair pasta.  That would be good but sadly no shrimp only plate.  My wife did not like her dish.  She said the cannelloni and filling were tasteless with an uninspired sauce.  Luckily her cannelloni dish was a 'special' and not on the regular menu for future diners.  The caveat... atmosphere.  The downstairs is nice but the upstairs was pleasant... for a bit.  A large rowdy group of sports fans came in near the end of our meal and drowned out the music and destroyed any semblance of upscale Italian dining.   The couple at the table next to us looked like they were on a nice date and then shortly looked miserable being unable to hear themselves talk, much less think.  Luckily my wife and I were done with our meal.  I asked my wife if she wanted dessert and she promptly said 'not here.'  It saddened me since I enjoyed my dish quite a lot and wanted to try their dessert but having a conversation became impossible with the recently changed 'atmosphere.'  I think everyone should try this great restaurant and I recommend the steak.  The caveat is don't go here for a 'date' on days when the sports game just ended.  I do like this place a lot and would like to go back on a quieter night.  The service, waitstaff,  hostess were all very nice and friendly.

We were from out of town and wanted to chat after our meal but the waiter and bus boy we're ready to pounce and get us out of there to turn over the table and get someone else there. So we just felt pretty rushed. The meal below was $26.00, it was pretty good, White wine sauce, noodles, mussels, 2 shrimp, calamari (undercooked) and 1 scallop.

Mia Francesca has a great wine list, wonderful food, and great service. It's not an Italian/American chicken parm kinda place. The menu is filled with fresh pastas, pizza, meats, and fish and is always wonderful. They also have a really good brunch on the weekends that doesn't get as crowded as some of the cookie cutter places closeby that the hangover crowd tends to frequent.

Extremely tiny place with forgetful servers. It seemed as if as many tables possible were smashed into a space the size of a 2 bedroom apartment. We had to ask for silverware, napkins, straws, the check as well as butter for the bread. Also we were seated next a huge and obnoxious party, neither the servers or other patrons wanted to be near. Food took forever and was not memorable or special. Won't be coming back.
Awesome food. Great place to grab a meal before a Cubs game

An old favorite!  On our recent visit to the Windy City, Mia Francesca did not disappoint.  Just as good as we remembered it with enormous portions.  All tasty!  Try the classic favorites... you'll be glad you did.
Excellent
Best restaurant
Delicious meal, loved the pasta and the amazing tiramisu. A bit on the pricier side, but I'd come back nonetheless.

Food was good however there was a limited menu. We had to ask to have our table changed because the waiters were swearing at the cooks. There is a nice out door patio, coach house and second floor which I wished they would have offered since the first floor was very loud and extremely overcrowded.
A favorite in the neighborhood!

The food is great but between my experiences (3 dinners) and that of the rest of my family (3 or 4), we received good service all of one time. When they remember they seated you, you have a better chance of being served. They generally just forget you, you ask someone to take your order, and then someone who seems not be a server takes your order and serves you. On two occasions, they delivered our table free cocktails, of their choice, as consolation. By then, however, we were annoyed and not sure we'd ever come back. Too bad, we live right around the corner and now we don't even consider it.
Good food but very tightly packed and way too loud inside.
Try the Pollo Arosto. Good food make a reservation so you don't have to wait in the small space.

Pricey ... so check out the menu before you sit down. But a must if you're in the market for fine dining. Great date night dinner. Menu is ever changing so you'll get a variety of options. Take the wife!

the staff answering the phone never know what's on the menu.  have called multiple times many times over many months to ask about specific daily items, staff can never answer with information specific to the day's menu.

This restaurant tends to be crowded most nights.  The seating is very cramped which is ok depending who you end up sitting next to.  The food was better than most Italian Restaurants I have been to in Chicago.  I had Risotto Con Capesante for a starter then the salmon for the main course.  The salmon was good but it is pretty hard to mess up salmon.  My date had spaghetti all Arlechino that looked really good and what I will probably order if I ever go back.  If you want a loud, lively restaurant this is a good choice.
Great food..
One of my favorite restaurants, their lemon chicken (not on the menu) is the best thing they have going.
A great little neighborhood spot with delicious pasta and appetizers. The prosciutto with melon is a must-have every time I go. Get reservations, this place fills up.

A neighborhood staple! We've been coming here to celebrate friend's birthdays for years.  Two weeks ago I was here with a group of 5.  Despite having a reservation our table touches the kitchen service bar, but the high traffic spot did not detract from the food.  They have great salads and we ordered a bunch of starters to share - the string bean, tomato and onion salad is fresh and delicious, the tomato onion and blue cheese, bruschetta with roasted butternut squash and baked goat cheese with pesto crustini.   My friend and I split two entrees from the daily specials list and they divided them in the kitchen (a much appreciated touch for splitters!) We shared great filet medallions and a fettucini Bolognese. Their menu changes seasonally but you cant go wrong dining at Mia Francesca anytime of year.

Some things were good, others were a bit like being at a nice diner. Our waitress was overwhelmed and not attentive. I also found her a bit pushy. For appetizers, the burrata  was good (i'm picky about burrata and this was better than I expected). Prosciutto was good but not the higher quality prosciutto. Brushette was fine, and butternut squash risotto was a bit bland. For the entrees, everyone had pastas which were generous in portion size. However, I found it disappointing that other than two pastas which were fresh pastas, the rest were dry/boxed. As for dessert, they had a pumpkin special which was probably the best thing we had all night. Chocolate lava cake was good as well.

The menu is inspired but the seating is so cramped that you want to rush through dinner to get away from the noise. I felt like I was dining with two other tables because there's no personal space boundaries.
favorite place to eat in Chicago
I LOVE Mia Francesca, it always has great food and great service. The only negative thing I have to say is that it is a little loud. Other than that, it is great place for all events
Classic italian taste for a great ambiance

It was the first time I went to Mia Francesca, really nice place to eat. Family oriented and the food was delicious. I ordered the Rigatoni with Pollo it was a great dish, I really recommended it. The whole place was great. I'm going back again.

Brought my Nana here, and she is the critics of all critics. She kept her sunglasses on the entire time, but that's a good thing. She did think she would chip a tooth on the rolls but she LOVED IT. And that is saying a lot. Great atmosphere, great good.

Mia Francesca is a great place for family dinners or dates.  The food is constantly amazing and the service is excellent.  They have a great wine list and the cheese ravioli is to die for.  It is in a close location to the el and there are tons of bars nearby for post-dinner drinks.  They also have a private party room in the back if you have a larger party which is a really great perk.
i came here for bff bday had a great time. the place and service was wonderful.  I had the mussles and salomon for dinner great birthday place for small parties

This place is awesome! It's usually pretty crowded on the weekends so I recommend making a reservation in advance. Their menu changes every month but they are awesome about letting you order whatever you can think of off the menu. The portions are huge and we always have leftovers for at least one or two lunches a person afterward. The ambiance is great too--its a great place for a date!
Good italian plates w/ nice wine selection
Love this place, my favorite Italian food in Chicago.  This location a bit noisy & crowded.
Great Italian food and nice deco. Service is always good. Real Italian food like the ones you get from Italy.

The "Coach-house" is actually a 2 car garage. You can see the bricks laid down to cover where the garage door was from the alley. I actually liked being in the coach house or the upstairs. Its quieter, less hectic and if you eat at the bar …

My absolute favorite Italian place in the city. Been going for years. Stellar service. Great and tasty food. The menu is limited but who needs a million things to pick from? Every item is awesome. A great, classy place to take a girl on a date. .... oh yeah almost forgot.... TRY THE TIRAMISU
Best Italian food in ALL of Chicago.  Warm Lentil App is amazing.  Love this place!

Went there on a monday and the restaurant was almost half full however we were told it would  be a 30- 60 min wait. Maybe they were expecting a party of 50 to show up any minute but my guess is they didn't want us as customers. That's fine I spent my money elsewhere.
Warm atmosphere, generous helpings, and great service.

Food was great and so was the service. But the atmosphere was pretty awful. We were put in the back room past the patio. And it was a very cozy little nook. I was excited for a lovely evening of good food in a cozy ambiance. However, the latter part of that wish was never met. The entire time we were there we were forced to listen to 70s disco music and it was god awful! Blaring Bee Gees, Gloria Gayner, Elton John in a "tuscan-style" restaurant was highly inappropriate and disturbing. No matter how good the food, I would never go there again due to the horrible music. I hope this owner understands that this restaurant does not call for disco, but rather soothing dinner music. If they change this, I'll be back.
